INSTALL ($Id$)
=======

To build chaos just type 'make build' in this directory after having unpacked the snapshot or checked the source out from CVS. Once you have ran 'make build', you can thereafter run 'make all' to rebuild chaos. The built kernels, libraries, servers and programs will be created in a chaos filesystem located under ./root. To change this (build directly to a mounted chaos partition or alike), edit the makefile and change the line INSTALL_PATH=...

Questions, bug reports and general feedback go to staff@chaosdev.org or the appropriate mailing list. Please check out http://www.chaosdev.org/ if you feel unsure about anything.
